Ad [Addendum] Problems around Bruegel. The fact that the majority of prints after Bruegel bears Latin texts speaks for connection with humanists. But there is a number of prints with French and/or Flemish inscriptions. One would have to draw up lists of the various kinds to establish the significance of the use of the various languages.

column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] Problems around Bruegel. The fact that the majority of prints after Bruegel bears Latin texts speaks for connection with humanists. But there is a number of prints with French and/or Flemish inscriptions. One would have to draw up lists of the various kinds to establish the significance of the use of the various languages.</content>
